---
import Layout from "@/layouts/Layout.astro";
---

<Layout locale="en">
	<section class="py-12 sm:py-16 md:py-20 lg:py-24">
		<div class="mx-auto max-w-4xl px-4 sm:px-6 lg:px-8">
			<h1 class="text-3xl sm:text-4xl md:text-5xl font-bold leading-tight text-foreground mb-8 sm:mb-12">
				Privacy Policy
			</h1>

			<div class="prose prose-lg dark:prose-invert max-w-none space-y-8">
				<!-- 1. Controller -->
				<div>
					<h2 class="text-2xl font-semibold text-foreground mb-4">1. Controller</h2>
					<p class="text-muted-foreground leading-relaxed">
						Jonas Westphal<br />
						<!-- Please add: Street and house number --><br />
						<!-- Please add: Postal code and city --><br />
						Email: kontakt@jonaswestphal.de
					</p>
					<p class="text-sm text-muted-foreground/70 italic leading-relaxed">
						Note: Please add the full postal address before publishing.
					</p>
				</div>

				<!-- 2. Hosting and CDN (Cloudflare) -->
				<div>
					<h2 class="text-2xl font-semibold text-foreground mb-4">2. Hosting and CDN (Cloudflare)</h2>
					<p class="text-muted-foreground leading-relaxed">
						This website is hosted by Cloudflare, Inc., 101 Townsend St, San Francisco, CA 94107, USA, and delivered via their Content Delivery Network (CDN).
					</p>
					<p class="text-muted-foreground leading-relaxed">
						<strong class="text-foreground">Services used:</strong> Cloudflare Pages (hosting), Content Delivery Network (CDN), Web Application Firewall (WAF), and additional security services.
					</p>
					<p class="text-muted-foreground leading-relaxed">
						<strong class="text-foreground">Data processed:</strong> IP address, request metadata (browser type, operating system, referrer URL, timestamp), security data (e.g., for attack detection).
					</p>
					<p class="text-muted-foreground leading-relaxed">
						<strong class="text-foreground">Purpose:</strong> Performance optimization, availability, security, and abuse prevention.
					</p>
					<p class="text-muted-foreground leading-relaxed">
						<strong class="text-foreground">Legal basis:</strong> Art. 6(1)(f) GDPR (legitimate interest in the secure and efficient provision of our website).
					</p>
					<p class="text-muted-foreground leading-relaxed">
						A Data Processing Agreement (DPA) is part of the contractual arrangements with Cloudflare. Data transfers to the USA are based on Standard Contractual Clauses (SCC) of the European Commission pursuant to Art. 46(2)(c) GDPR.
					</p>
				</div>

				<!-- 3. Server Log Files -->
				<div>
					<h2 class="text-2xl font-semibold text-foreground mb-4">3. Server Log Files</h2>
					<p class="text-muted-foreground leading-relaxed">
						The hosting provider automatically collects and stores information in server log files that your browser transmits automatically. This includes:
					</p>
					<ul class="list-disc list-inside text-muted-foreground leading-relaxed space-y-1 ml-4">
						<li>IP address of the accessing device</li>
						<li>Date and time of the request (timestamp)</li>
						<li>Browser type and version</li>
						<li>Operating system</li>
						<li>Referrer URL (previously visited page)</li>
					</ul>
					<p class="text-muted-foreground leading-relaxed">
						This data is not merged with other data sources.
					</p>
					<p class="text-muted-foreground leading-relaxed">
						<strong class="text-foreground">Legal basis:</strong> Art. 6(1)(f) GDPR (legitimate interest in the technical provision and security of the website).
					</p>
				</div>

				<!-- 4. Cloudflare Analytics (cookieless) -->
				<div>
					<h2 class="text-2xl font-semibold text-foreground mb-4">4. Cloudflare Web Analytics</h2>
					<p class="text-muted-foreground leading-relaxed">
						This website uses Cloudflare Web Analytics in cookieless mode. No cookies are set and no personal data is collected that would allow identification of individual users. Only aggregated usage statistics are recorded (e.g., page views, time on site, device types used).
					</p>
					<p class="text-muted-foreground leading-relaxed">
						Since no cookies are set and no personal identification occurs, no consent pursuant to § 25 TTDSG (German Telecommunications-Telemedia Data Protection Act) is required for Cloudflare Web Analytics.
					</p>
					<p class="text-muted-foreground leading-relaxed">
						<strong class="text-foreground">Legal basis:</strong> Art. 6(1)(f) GDPR (legitimate interest in the anonymous analysis of user behavior to improve the website).
					</p>
				</div>

				<!-- 5. Google Analytics (GA4) – with consent -->
				<div>
					<h2 class="text-2xl font-semibold text-foreground mb-4">5. Google Analytics (GA4)</h2>
					<p class="text-muted-foreground leading-relaxed">
						This website uses Google Analytics 4, a web analytics service provided by Google Ireland Limited, Gordon House, Barrow Street, Dublin 4, Ireland (hereinafter "Google").
					</p>
					<p class="text-muted-foreground leading-relaxed">
						Google Analytics is <strong class="text-foreground">only loaded after your explicit consent</strong> via the cookie banner (opt-in). Without your consent, no tracking takes place.
					</p>
					<p class="text-muted-foreground leading-relaxed">
						<strong class="text-foreground">Configuration:</strong> IP anonymization is enabled, Google Signals is disabled, ad personalization is disabled, and data retention is set to the minimum.
					</p>
					<p class="text-muted-foreground leading-relaxed">
						<strong class="text-foreground">Data processed:</strong> Usage behavior, page views, time on site, device and browser information.
					</p>
					<p class="text-muted-foreground leading-relaxed">
						<strong class="text-foreground">Legal basis:</strong> Art. 6(1)(a) GDPR (consent).
					</p>
					<p class="text-muted-foreground leading-relaxed">
						<strong class="text-foreground">Right of withdrawal:</strong> You can withdraw your consent at any time with effect for the future by clicking the "Cookie Settings" link in the website footer and changing your selection.
					</p>
					<p class="text-muted-foreground leading-relaxed">
						Data transfers to the USA are based on Standard Contractual Clauses (SCC) of the European Commission. A Data Processing Agreement (DPA) is in place with Google.
					</p>
				</div>

				<!-- 6. Cookies and Consent (TTDSG) -->
				<div>
					<h2 class="text-2xl font-semibold text-foreground mb-4">6. Cookies and Consent (TTDSG)</h2>
					<p class="text-muted-foreground leading-relaxed">
						This website uses an opt-in model pursuant to § 25 TTDSG (German Telecommunications-Telemedia Data Protection Act). On your first visit, you will be informed about the use of cookies via a cookie banner and asked for your consent.
					</p>
					<p class="text-muted-foreground leading-relaxed">
						<strong class="text-foreground">Technically necessary storage (no consent required):</strong>
					</p>
					<ul class="list-disc list-inside text-muted-foreground leading-relaxed space-y-1 ml-4">
						<li>Consent storage (localStorage) – stores your cookie decision</li>
						<li>Theme preference (localStorage) – stores your choice between light and dark mode</li>
					</ul>
					<p class="text-muted-foreground leading-relaxed">
						<strong class="text-foreground">Analytics cookies (only with explicit consent):</strong>
					</p>
					<ul class="list-disc list-inside text-muted-foreground leading-relaxed space-y-1 ml-4">
						<li>Google Analytics – only loaded after your consent</li>
					</ul>
					<p class="text-muted-foreground leading-relaxed">
						No tracking takes place before consent is given. No checkboxes are pre-selected. You can withdraw your consent at any time via the "Cookie Settings" link in the website footer.
					</p>
				</div>

				<!-- 7. Contact Form (Cloudflare Worker) -->
				<div>
					<h2 class="text-2xl font-semibold text-foreground mb-4">7. Contact Form</h2>
					<p class="text-muted-foreground leading-relaxed">
						When you contact us via the contact form, the following data is collected (data minimization):
					</p>
					<ul class="list-disc list-inside text-muted-foreground leading-relaxed space-y-1 ml-4">
						<li>Name</li>
						<li>Email address</li>
						<li>Message</li>
					</ul>
					<p class="text-muted-foreground leading-relaxed">
						The data is processed via a Cloudflare Worker and forwarded to us by email via Amazon SES. No unnecessary logging of submitted data takes place. Transmission is encrypted via HTTPS.
					</p>
					<p class="text-muted-foreground leading-relaxed">
						<strong class="text-foreground">Legal basis:</strong> Art. 6(1)(b) GDPR (performance of pre-contractual measures at the request of the data subject) or Art. 6(1)(f) GDPR (legitimate interest in processing inquiries).
					</p>
				</div>

				<!-- 8. Cloudflare Turnstile (Bot Protection) -->
				<div>
					<h2 class="text-2xl font-semibold text-foreground mb-4">8. Cloudflare Turnstile (Bot Protection)</h2>
					<p class="text-muted-foreground leading-relaxed">
						To protect our contact form against automated requests (bots), we use Cloudflare Turnstile.
					</p>
					<p class="text-muted-foreground leading-relaxed">
						<strong class="text-foreground">Data processed:</strong> IP address, behavioral data (e.g., mouse movements, keyboard input to distinguish humans from bots).
					</p>
					<p class="text-muted-foreground leading-relaxed">
						<strong class="text-foreground">Purpose:</strong> Abuse prevention and protection against automated requests.
					</p>
					<p class="text-muted-foreground leading-relaxed">
						<strong class="text-foreground">Legal basis:</strong> Art. 6(1)(f) GDPR (legitimate interest in protection against abuse).
					</p>
				</div>

				<!-- 9. Third Country Transfer (USA) -->
				<div>
					<h2 class="text-2xl font-semibold text-foreground mb-4">9. Third Country Transfer (USA)</h2>
					<p class="text-muted-foreground leading-relaxed">
						Cloudflare, Inc. and Google Ireland Limited (or their parent company Google LLC) are based in or process data in the USA. The USA is considered a third country within the meaning of the GDPR.
					</p>
					<p class="text-muted-foreground leading-relaxed">
						Data transfers to the USA are based on Standard Contractual Clauses (SCC) of the European Commission pursuant to Art. 46(2)(c) GDPR. Data Processing Agreements (DPA) are in place with both providers.
					</p>
				</div>

				<!-- 10. Your Rights (Data Subject Rights) -->
				<div>
					<h2 class="text-2xl font-semibold text-foreground mb-4">10. Your Rights (Data Subject Rights)</h2>
					<p class="text-muted-foreground leading-relaxed">
						You have the following rights with regard to your personal data:
					</p>
					<ul class="list-disc list-inside text-muted-foreground leading-relaxed space-y-1 ml-4">
						<li><strong class="text-foreground">Right of access</strong> (Art. 15 GDPR)</li>
						<li><strong class="text-foreground">Right to rectification</strong> (Art. 16 GDPR)</li>
						<li><strong class="text-foreground">Right to erasure</strong> (Art. 17 GDPR)</li>
						<li><strong class="text-foreground">Right to restriction of processing</strong> (Art. 18 GDPR)</li>
						<li><strong class="text-foreground">Right to data portability</strong> (Art. 20 GDPR)</li>
						<li><strong class="text-foreground">Right to object</strong> (Art. 21 GDPR)</li>
						<li><strong class="text-foreground">Right to withdraw consent</strong> (Art. 7(3) GDPR) – without affecting the lawfulness of processing based on consent before its withdrawal</li>
						<li><strong class="text-foreground">Right to lodge a complaint with a supervisory authority</strong> – You have the right to lodge a complaint with a data protection supervisory authority regarding the processing of your personal data</li>
					</ul>
					<p class="text-muted-foreground leading-relaxed">
						To exercise your rights, please contact: <a href="mailto:kontakt@jonaswestphal.de" class="text-primary hover:underline">kontakt@jonaswestphal.de</a>
					</p>
				</div>
			</div>
		</div>
	</section>
</Layout>
